            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Cup-of-tea-1651582507333-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Cup-of-tea-1651582507333-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Cup-of-tea-1651582507333-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Cup-of-tea-1651582507333-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Cup-of-tea-1651582507333-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>After 20 min, remove the dish from the oven and add the<strong> </strong>juice<strong> </strong>of 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>lime</strong>, 1 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>haddock bites </strong>(unevenly sized haddock bites? Chop any larger ones into bite-sized pieces!) and return the dish to the oven for 4-5 min or until the haddock is cooked through – this is your<strong> all-in-one fragrant coconutty haddock curry</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>lime</strong> into wedges</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1604418786935-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1604418786935-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1604418786935-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1604418786935-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1604418786935-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To serve, tear the<strong> coriander </strong>over the <strong>all-in-one</strong> <strong>fragrant coconutty haddock curry</strong></p><p>Garnish with a<strong> lime wedge</strong></p><p>Tip: Watch out for the ginger halves and lemongrass, discard them!</p><p>Let everyone dig in!</p>",
      "order": 8,
